{
  "texts": [
    "The fully connected layers in the CNN necessitate resizing images to a fixed size of 277 × 277, which increases computational overhead.",
    "The selective search algorithm generates thousands of potential regions, resulting in inefficiencies and high computation time.",
    "Additionally, processing these regions individually leads to redundant computations, and the SVM-based classification introduces bottlenecks that hinder speed and optimization.",
    "These challenges limit RCNN's performance in real-time applications, complex image backgrounds, and small object detection.",
    "To address these issues, several advancements have been proposed."
  ]
}